# GenAI Gurus — Project Rules

## Technology
- Astro + Tailwind CSS, static output, GitHub Pages compatible.
- No server-side rendering, no databases, no CMS.

## Design
- Do NOT use generic AI startup aesthetics (neon, glowing brains, robot heads, circuit patterns).
- Do NOT add pricing sections, testimonials, newsletter signups, or SaaS-style feature grids.
- Do NOT use clichéd AI visuals or sci-fi/crypto aesthetics.
- Keep the design editorial, clean, community-driven. Premium feel through typography, spacing, and curation — not visual noise.

## Information Architecture
- The landing page follows the section order defined in site-functional-spec.md:
  Hero → Upcoming Event → Highlighted Talks → Core Team → Milestones → About → Speak & Partner → Footer.
- The leaderboard lives at /leaderboard.
- No other pages unless explicitly required.

## Data
- Manual content lives in src/data/ (JSON) and src/content/ (Markdown).
- Generated data (stats, leaderboard, upcoming event) is written by GitHub Actions scripts.
- Highlighted talks are always manually curated — never auto-selected.

## Code Style
- Use Astro components in src/components/.
- Import data at build time in frontmatter.
- Prefer semantic HTML elements.
- Keep components focused — one section per component.
